hopobject.body: Best Site Good Work drugtreatments.info China has reported better than expected exports in August due to recovery in market conditions in United States and European Union. As per the customs records, the trade surplus was higher at USD 28.5 billion. The second largest economy in the world is showing signs of strength as the exports were higher and trade surplus was 8.4 percent higher compared to last year figures. China exported goods worth $190.6 billion during August, registering increase of 7.2 per compared to last year.
